  <h1>
   bool
  </h1>
  This function will attempt to convert a given value into a boolean data type, where the value will be returned as
  <span>
   true
  </span>
  if it is greater than or equal to 0.5, and
  <span>
   false
  </span>
  otherwise.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">bool(n);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      n
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The value to convert.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Boolean
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   <b>
    Example:
   </b>
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if !is_bool(val)
{
    val = bool(val);
}
</code></pre>
  The above code checks the variable "val" to see if it is a boolean and if it is not then it is converted to one.
 </body>
